      "id": 358650,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>1,6-Methanonaphthalene has an interesting <sup>1</sup>H NMR spectrum in which the eight hydrogens around the perimeter absorb at 6.9 to 7.3 <i>δ</i>, while the two CH<sub>2</sub> protons absorb at –0.5 <i>δ</i>. Tell whether it is aromatic, and explain its NMR spectrum.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaXNWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--daed64e9e90f4cf3b3e7e77b1a9f3a92afe5d81f/OChem_15_EC_003.jpg\" alt=\"The ball-and-stick model of 1,6-methanonaphthalene has a cycloheptatriene ring fused to a cycloheptadiene ring.\">\n",
